Last Updated: October 17, 2023
Welcome to Kumu!
Kumu Privacy Policy (v3.0)
At kumu, as part of our commitment to create a safe space, we are working our best to ensure that your privacy is respected and your Personal Data is protected.
Thus, we want you to take a moment and understand what data we obtain about you and our data privacy practices and policies, so you can make an informed decision and exercise meaningful control over your data.
This Privacy Policy will take effect on 20 Nov 2023. For the old version (v2.0) of the policy click
here
.
HIGHLIGHTS
You should read our Privacy Policy in its entirety, but here are a few key points we hope you will take away:
kumu is accessible to the general public from anywhere in the world except in a few countries where the service is unavailable in order for kumu to comply with the law or its company policy.
When you livestream, create a profile, follow a streamer, give virtual gifts, participate in campaigns or post a clip on kumu that are public or intended to be public in nature, individuals that use kumu will access this information and may have the ability to acquire, use, or reveal such information to others. Furthermore, several of our Services (as defined below) are intended to offer others with information on user behavior, such as virtual gifting or a follow to a streamer. We advise you to keep this in mind when using kumu. However, we also provide non-public communication channels on kumu, such as private streaming and chat.
When you participate in campaigns sponsored by our Business Partners (i.e. any company or individual which transacts business with Kumu, including but not limited to advertisers and merchants), we may share your Personal Data with them in accordance with the terms and conditions of the campaigns. For example, if you participate in DTI (Philippines) registered campaigns of a Business Partner, we may share your information with DTI (Philippines) as part our legal obligation and with the Business Partner as part of our contractual obligation.
When you purchase products from our Business Partners, we may share your Personal Data with them to fulfill your orders and to third party service providers for the delivery of your ordered products.
We collect certain Personal Data (e.g. information regarding the device you’re using, IP address, etc.) from you when you use kumu, even if you’re simply browsing livestreams. We use this information to keep the platform safe and to offer you more relevant content, suggested users and advertisements.
We want to hear from you if you have any concerns regarding this Privacy Policy, how we collect or use your Personal Data, or anything else relating to our policies or practices at kumu. You are welcome to contact us at any time using the contact details set out at the end of the Privacy Policy.
APPLICABILITY +
This Privacy Policy is applicable to the collection and use of Personal Data by KumuMedia International Pte. Ltd. (“kumu,” “we,” “us,” or “our”). It describes kumu’s practices regarding the collection, use, disclosure, sale and other processing of Personal Data when you:
Use kumu products and services (e.g. websites, applications, or services supplied, owned, or operated by kumu) which we refer to collectively in this Privacy Policy as our “Services,” or
Otherwise, communicate with us
Kumu acts as the “controller” of your Personal Data for the activities described in this Privacy Policy. That means kumu is the legal entity deciding why and how your Personal Data is collected and used.
EXTERNAL PARTY SITES
Our Services may contain links to other websites [and apps] that we do not operate, which may have privacy policies that differ from our own. If you click on a third party link, you may be directed to that third party’s website [or app landing page]. We strongly advise you to review the privacy policy of every third party site and/or app that you visit. We have no control over and assume no responsibility for the content, privacy policies or practices of any third party sites, apps or services.
WHAT PERSONAL DATA DO WE COLLECT
CATEGORIES AND SOURCES +
For purposes of this Privacy Policy, “Personal Data” means any data that identifies, relates to, describes, is reasonably capable of being associated with, or could reasonably be linked, directly or indirectly, with a particular consumer or household. This implies that Personal Data includes information that directly identifies you, such as your name, as well as information that can reasonably be used to identify you, such as your device number in certain circumstances. Personal data does not include aggregated data (which does not identify a particular individual).
We may collect the following categories of Personal Data from you when you [download our app], create an account, stream through our Services, participate in our campaigns and challenges, post klips, use our chat services, purchase coins and share virtual gifts through our Services, contact us (including via social media), participate in our surveys and events, purchase a product in our kumu shop, or otherwise interact with us by using our Services.
USER-PROVIDED PERSONAL DATA
Personal identifiers.
Name, email address, physical address, phone number, [social media account names], registered devices, gender, in-game username (for gaming tournaments and competitions) and age
Payment Information.
Information about billing address and payment method, such as bank account information, credit, debit, or other payment card information
Transaction Information.
Data about purchases and use of services or transactions facilitated by kumu, including purchases made through the Services
Usage Information.
Audio, videos, images, and other information uploaded, viewed ,shared and downloaded on and from the Services; interactions and exchanges with other users (e.g. chat, stream, etc.)
Government ID Data.
We may request a government-issued ID in some instances, such as for verification of your identity, or as required by law
Other Information You Provide to Us.
The content of your kumu correspondence, including exchanges with our customer support (including social media)
Inferences Drawn From your Data.
Inferences we make based upon your interests and viewing preferences
SENSITIVE INFORMATION
Sensitive Personal information are those personal data revealing racial or ethnic origin, political opinions, religious or philosophical beliefs; trade-union membership; genetic data, biometric data processed solely to identify a human being; health-related data; data concerning a person’s sex life or sexual orientation.
When necessary, with your consent or as otherwise permitted by applicable law, we may also process the following categories of sensitive information:
financial data
biometric data
social security numbers or other government identifiers
PAYMENT DATA
We may collect data necessary to process your payment if you make purchases, such as your payment instrument number, and the security code associated with your payment instrument.
SOCIAL MEDIA LOG-IN DATA
We may provide you with the option to register with us using your existing social media account details, like your Facebook, Twitter, or other social media account. If you choose to register this way, we will collect the information described herein.
APPLICATION DATA
When you use our mobile application(s), we may also collect the following information if you choose to provide us access and permission:
Geolocation Information.
We may request access or permission to track location-based information from your mobile device, either continuously or while you are using our mobile application(s), to provide certain location-based services. If you wish to change our access or permissions, you may do so in your device’s settings.
Mobile Device Access.
We may request access or permission to certain features from your mobile device, including your mobile device’s camera,contacts, microphone, bluetooth, calendar, reminders, sms messages, social media accounts, storage, and other features. If you wish to change our accessor permissions, you may do so in your device’s settings.
Push Notifications.
We may request to send you push notifications regarding your account or certain features of the application(s). If you wish to opt out from receiving these types of communications, you may turn them off in your device’s settings.
The above information is primarily needed to maintain the security and operation of our application(s), for troubleshooting, and for our internal analytics, and reporting purposes.
AUTOMATICALLY-COLLECTED DATA
When you use our Services, we use cookies and other technologies to automatically collect, record, store and otherwise process the following types of Personal Data:
Usage Data.
Data about your activities on and use of our Services, such as app launches inside our Services, browser history, product engagement, IP address or other unique identifiers, and other information regarding your interaction with our Services and our advertisements
Device Information.
Data that can be used to identify your device, such as the device ID, or information about the device, such as the browser type
We use Google Analytics to evaluate the use of our website. Google Analytics uses cookies and other identifiers to collect information, such as how often users visit a website, what pages they visit when they do so, and what other websites they visited prior to visiting a website. To learn more about how Google Analytics collects Personal Data, review
Google’s Privacy Policy
.
To learn more about cookies, please check our cookie policy
here
INFORMATION FROM OTHER SOURCES
kumu may receive Personal Data about you from other individuals, from businesses or third parties acting at your direction, from our Business Partners such as social media platforms with which you interact, and from third parties that work with us to provide our products and services and assist us with security and fraud prevention and improving our Services.
For instance, we may acquire your Personal Data from social media networks (such as Facebook). By accessing or connecting our Services through social media, you authorize kumu to collect, retain, and otherwise process such Personal Data in accordance with this Privacy Policy and our Terms of Use.
