Partner merchants.
When you purchase product from our kumu shop, we share your personal data with the shop merchants to fulfill your orders, process payment and delivery, return of your orders.
We may also share aggregated, anonymized data with our Business Partners and advertising clients, such as user segment statistics.
LAW AND PUBLIC INTEREST
We may disclose your Personal Data if we believe it is reasonably necessary to comply with law, regulation, legal process, or governmental requests such as court orders, subpoenas, or warrants in the manner allowed by law.
We may also disclose Personal Data when we believe, in good faith, that disclosure is appropriate or reasonably necessary to protect kumu from fraudulent, abusive, or unlawful uses; to investigate and defend ourselves against third-party claims or allegations; to protect the security or integrity of kumu; or to protect the rights, property, or safety of kumu, our users, or others.
AFFILIATES AND CHANGE OF OWNERSHIP
We may also disclose your Personal Data to kumu affiliates (companies controlled by, controlling, or under common control with kumu) and subsidiaries that are either subject to this Privacy Policy or implement standards that are at least as protective as those specified in this Privacy Policy.
Your Personal Data may also be transferred as part of a bankruptcy, merger, acquisition, reorganization, or sale of kumu assets if we are involved in such a transaction, including any evaluation of such a transaction.
HOW DOES KUMU OPERATE AND TRANSFER PERSONAL DATA GLOBALLY
Your information, including Personal Data, is processed at kumu’s operating offices and in any other places where the parties involved in the processing are located. It means that this information may be transferred to — and maintained on — computers/servers located outside of your state, province, country or other governmental jurisdiction where the data protection laws may differ than those from your jurisdiction.
kumu will take all steps reasonably necessary to ensure that your data is transferred securely and in accordance with this Privacy Policy, and applicable laws, and no transfer of your Personal Data will take place to an organization or a country unless there are adequate controls in place including with respect to the security of your Personal Data.
HOW LONG KUMU STORES YOUR PERSONAL DATA
kumu will retain your Personal Data only for as long as is necessary for the purposes set out in this Privacy Policy or as required or permitted by applicable laws. We will retain and use your Personal Data to the extent necessary to comply with our legal obligations (for example, if we are required to retain your data to comply with applicable laws), resolve disputes, and enforce our contractual agreements and policies.
We will cease to retain your Personal Data, or remove the means by which the data can be associated with you, as soon as it is reasonable to assume that such retention no longer serves the purpose for which the Personal Data was collected, and is no longer necessary for legal or business purposes.
HOW KUMU SECURES YOUR PERSONAL DATA
To safeguard your Personal Data from unauthorized access, collection, use, disclosure, copying, modification, disposal or similar risks, we have put in place reasonable and appropriate administrative, physical and technical measures.
You should be aware, however, that no method of transmission over the Internet or method of electronic storage is completely secure. Data security incidents and breaches can occur due to a variety of factors that cannot reasonably be prevented; therefore, our safeguards may not always be adequate to prevent all breaches of security.
YOUR PRIVACY RIGHTS AND MANAGING YOUR PERSONAL DATA
CALIFORNIA RESIDENTS
California residents may have specific rights with respect to the Personal Data we collect.  Click [here] for additional information about California residents’ rights and disclosures of our privacy practices as required under applicable California law.
PRIVACY RIGHTS
We generally rely on Personal Data provided by you (or your authorized representative). In order to ensure that your Personal Data is current, complete and accurate, please update us if there are changes to your Personal Data.
Subject to certain restrictions and limitations, you have certain rights in respect of your Personal Data. In particular, you have the following rights:
Right to access
– to receive a copy of your Personal Data. We will have to adequately verify your identity before any action can be taken;
Right to rectification
– to request for amendments to be made to your Personal Data where this is inaccurate or incorrect;
Right to restriction –
to ask that we restrict or suppress the processing of your Personal Data which means that whilst we are permitted to store the Personal Data we cannot otherwise process it;
Right to erasure
– to request for the deletion of your Personal Data that we hold. However, we may not always be able to delete your Personal Data for legal and regulatory reasons;
Right to object
– to object to the processing of your Personal Data which we carry out in reliance on our legitimate interests. In such instances, we will investigate to see if there is compelling reason for processing to continue. You cannot object to the processing which is a legal obligation or where we must process your Personal Data to satisfy a contract to which you are a party. Also, you can object to marketing communications at any time;
Right to withdraw you consent
– to withdraw your consent to the processing of your Personal Data at any time (where kumu is processing your personal information based on your consent). Please note that withdrawing your consent may prevent us from further providing all or part of our Services to you but does not affect the lawfulness of our processing of your Personal Data based on such consent before the withdrawal;
Right to data portability
– to receive certain Personal Data that you have provided to us, in a machine-readable form and/or that we transmit it to a third party with your express authorisation; and
Right to lodge a complaint
–to complain to the relevant supervisory authority if your privacy rights are violated, or if you have suffered as a result of unlawful processing of your Personal Data.
We may ask you for identifying information and attempt to match it to information that we maintain about you. If we can’t verify your identity or authority to make the request, and confirm the Personal Data belongs to you, we won’t be able to complete your request. We will notify you to inform you of this. You do not need to create an account with us to make a verifiable request. Personal data submitted in a verifiable request will only be used to confirm the requestor’s identity or permission to make the request.
If you would like to exercise your rights, please contact the Data Protection Officer using the contact details below.
To the extent permitted under applicable data protection laws, we may charge a reasonable fee for an access request to cover our administrative costs of providing the information in certain situations.  If so, we will inform you of the fee before we proceed with your request.
We will respond to your request as soon as reasonably possible and within thirty (30) calendar days. Should we not be able to respond to your request within thirty (30) days after receiving your request and where we are permitted to do so under applicable data protection laws, we will inform you in writing within thirty (30) days of the time by which we will be able to respond to your request.
ADDITIONAL INFORMATION OR ASSISTANCE
To protect your privacy and implement security, we will take reasonable steps to verify your identity before granting your request. We reserve the right to charge an appropriate fee for complying with your request where allowed by applicable law. There may be situations where we cannot grant your request especially if it jeopardizes the privacy of others, is frivolous or vexatious, or would be extremely impractical.
CHILDREN’S PRIVACY
kumu recognizes and values the importance of protecting the privacy of children, which we define as anyone under the age of thirteen. Our Services are not intended for or directed to children under the age of thirteen, and anyone under the age of thirteen are not permitted to use kumu. If we discover that we are processing data for such users (under the age of 13), we shall take reasonable steps to guarantee that their records are erased and data processing is ceased. Please inform us if you suspect we have Personal Data about or acquired from a child under the age of 13.
You must also be of legal age in your country to consent to the processing of your Personal Data (in some countries we may allow your parent or guardian to do so on your behalf).
ACCESSIBILITY
We are committed to ensuring that our communications are accessible to people with disabilities.  To make accessibility-related requests or report barriers, please contact us at dpo@kumu.ph.
CHANGES
We may revise this Privacy Policy from time to time without any prior notice. You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes. You may determine if any such revision has taken place by referring to the date on which this Privacy Policy was last updated.
If we make material changes to the Privacy Policy, we will let you know via email and/or a prominent notice on our Service, prior to the change becoming effective and update the date at the top of this Privacy Policy. Your continued use of our services constitutes your acknowledgement and acceptance of such changes.
CONTACT
You may contact our Data Protection Officer if you have any inquiries or feedback on our Personal Data protection policies and procedures, or if you wish to make any request, in the following manner:
Data Protection Officer
dpo@kumu.ph, 6F Robinsons Cybergate Tower 3, Pioneer St., Mandaluyong City, Philippines.
