CALIFORNIA PRIVACY NOTICE
This California Privacy Notice(“California Notice” or “Notice”) supplements the Privacy Policy above and applies to California residents.  It describes our data collection practices with respect to the Personal Data we collect about California residents when they use our Services, communicate to us and engage with us offline.  The Notice also describes rights California residents have with respect to the Personal Data we collect.
Terms that are defined in the Privacy Policy have the same meaning when used in this California Notice.
Categories of Personal Data We Collect and Have Collected in the Past 12 Months – Sources and Categories
In the 12 months preceding the date of this California Notice, we may have collected your Personal Data when you download our app, create an account, stream through our Services, participate in our campaigns and challenges, post klips, use our chat services, purchase coins and share virtual gifts through our Services, contact us (including via social media), participate in our surveys and events, purchase a product in our kumu shop, or otherwise interact with us by using our Services.  We will continue to collect Personal Data from the same sources.
In the  twelve (12) months prior to the date of this Notice, we have collected, and will continue to collect, the following categories of Personal Data:
Personal Identifiers
: Name, physical address, phone number, unique personal identifier, IP address, device ID, email address, in-game username, account name and password, [social media account names], governmental ID information
Financial information:
Bank account information, credit, debit, or other payment card information
Protected class information
: Gender, age range
Commercial information:
Records of products or Services purchased or consumed
Internet or other electronic network activity:
Data about your activities on and use of our Services, app launches inside our Services, browser history, search history, and product engagement, information regarding your interaction with our Services and our advertisements, device and browser type
Audio and visual information:
Audio, videos, images, and other information uploaded, viewed ,shared and downloaded on and from the Services; interactions and exchanges with other users (e.g., chat, stream)
Inferences drawn from any of the Personal Data identified above
.
Purposes for Collection of Personal Data
We use your Personal Data for the following purposes to provide Services to you; to perform our obligations in the course of or in connection with our Services requested by you; to allow you to leave comments on content and engage in campaigns or rewards programs; to verify your identity and respond to, handle, and process queries, requests, applications, complaints, and feedback from you; to process payment or credit transactions; to provide you with news, special offers and general information about our Services.
We also use your Personal Data to comply with any applicable laws, regulations, codes of practice, guidelines, or rules, or to assist in law enforcement and investigations conducted by any governmental and/or regulatory authority. This includes, but is not limited to, as applicable, disclosure of Personal Data of the winners of DTI registered campaigns to Philippines’ Department of Trade and Industry, and processing your Personal Data in accordance to the regulatory requirements of Anti-Money Laundering Council and Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas.
Additionally, we use Personal Data to monitor or improve our Services; for internal business analysis; to prevent fraud, activities that violate our Terms of Service or that are illegal; and to protect our rights and the rights and safety of our users or others.
Categories of Personal Data Disclosed for Business Purpose in Past 12 Months
Categories of Consumers’ Personal Data
Categories of Third Parties With Which We Shared Personal Data for a Business Purpose
Personal Identifiers: Name, physical address, phone number, unique personal identifier, IP address, device ID, email address, in-game username, account name and password, [social media account names], governmental ID information
Service providers that
assist us in operating, analyzing, and displaying content on our website; provide analytics information; advertise or market our products; provide website hosting, webcast and teleconference services; provide legal and accounting services.
Financial information: Bank account information, credit, debit, or other payment card information
Service providers that provide payment processing services
Commercial information:
Records of products or Services purchased or consumed
Service providers that assist kumu in improving the kumu Services and developing new services and features; fulfill and/or distribute orders or contest prizes; and conduct data analysis and report creation
Internet or other electronic network activity:
Data about your activities on and use of our Services, app launches inside our Services, browser history, search history, and product engagement, information regarding your interaction with our Services and our advertisements, device and browser type
Service providers that provide data security services and cloud-based data storage; host our website and assist with other IT-related functions; advertise and market our products; and provide analytics information
Additional Information About How We May Disclose Personal Data
We may also disclose your Personal Data as required or permitted by law, to comply with a subpoena or similar legal process or government request, or when we believe in good faith that disclosure is legally required or otherwise necessary to protect our rights and property or the rights, property or safety of others, including to law enforcement agencies, and judicial and regulatory authorities. We may also share your Personal Data with third parties to help detect and protect against fraud or data security vulnerabilities.  And we may transfer your Personal Data to a third party in the event of an actual or contemplated sale, merger, reorganization of our entity or other restructuring.
Rights Regarding Personal Data
Your Right To Request Disclosure of Information We Collect and Share About You
We are committed to ensuring that you know what Personal Data we collect. To that end, you can ask us for any or all of following types of information regarding the Personal Data we have collected about you in the 12 months prior to our receipt of your request:
Specific pieces of Personal Data we have collected about you;
Categories of Personal Data we have collected about you;
Categories of sources from which such Personal Data was collected;
Categories of Personal Data that the business sold or disclosed for a business purpose about the consumer;
Categories of third parties to whom the Personal Data was sold or disclosed for a business purpose; and
The business or commercial purpose for collecting or selling your Personal Data.
Your Right To Request Deletion of Personal Data We Have Collected About You
Upon your request, we will delete the Personal Data we have collected about you, except for situations where the CCPA authorizes us to retain specific information, including when it is necessary for us to provide you with a good or service that you requested; perform a contract we entered into with you; maintain the functionality or security of our systems; or comply with or exercise rights provided by the law.  The law also permits us to retain specific information for our exclusively internal use, but only in ways that are compatible with the context in which you provided the information to us or that are reasonably aligned with your expectations based on your relationship with us.  We will act on your deletion request within the timeframes set forth below.
Your Right to Ask Us Not to Sell Personal Data We Have Collected About You
You can direct us not to sell your Personal Data by submitting an opt-out request through our Data Request Form , or by contacting us.  We will act on your request within the timeframes set forth below.
Exercising Your Rights and How We Will Respond
To exercise any of the rights above, or to ask a question, contact us, complete and submit our Data Request Form or use the contact details set out at the end of this California Notice .
For requests for access or deletion, we will first acknowledge receipt of your request within 10 business days of receipt of your request.  We provide a substantive response to your request as soon as we can, generally within 45 days from when we receive your request, although we may be allowed to take longer to process your request under certain circumstances.  If we expect your request is going to take us longer than normal to fulfill, we will let you know.
For requests to stop the sale of your Personal Data, we will comply no later than 15 business days after receipt of your request.
We usually act on requests and provide information free of charge, but we may charge a reasonable fee to cover our administrative costs of providing the information in certain situations.  In some cases, the law may allow us to refuse to act on certain requests.  When this is the case, we will endeavor to provide you with an explanation as to why.
Verification of Identity – Access or Deletion Requests
We will ask you for identifying information and attempt to match it to information that we maintain about you.
If we are unable to verify your identity with the degree of certainty required, we will not be able to respond to your request.  We will notify you to explain the basis of the denial.
Ensuring Veracity of Opt-Out Requests
If we have a good-faith, reasonable belief that a request to opt-out of the sale of Personal Data is fraudulent, we may deny the request.  Should this occur, we will inform you and explain why we believe the request is fraudulent.
Authorized Agents
You may designate an agent to submit requests on your behalf.  The agent must be a natural person or a business entity that is registered with the California Secretary of State.
If you would like to designate an agent to act on your behalf, you and the agent will need to comply with our verification process:
Requests to Know or Delete Personal Data:
If the agent submits requests to access, know or delete your Personal Data, the agent will need to provide us with your signed permission indicating the agent has been authorized to submit the opt-out request on your behalf.  We will also require that you verify your identity directly with us or confirm with us that you provided the agent with permission to submit the request.
Requests to Opt Out of Sale:
If the agent submits a request to opt out of the sale of your Personal Data, the agent will need to provide us with your signed permission indicating the agent has been authorized to submit the opt-out request on your behalf.
Please note that this subsection does not apply when an agent is authorized to act on your behalf pursuant to a valid power of attorney.  Any such requests will be processed in accordance with California law pertaining to powers of attorney.
Requests for Household Information
There may be some types of Personal Data that can be associated with a household (a group of people living together in a single dwelling).  Requests for access or deletion of household Personal Data must be made by each member of the household.  To the extent we collect household information and requests are made pertaining specifically to such information, before responding to a request, we will verify the identity of each member of the household using the verification criteria explained above and will also verify that each household member is currently a member of the household.
No discrimination for exercise of CCPA rights
We will not discriminate against you for exercising any of your CCPA rights. Unless the CCPA allows it, we will not deny your use of our services.
California “Shine the Light” disclosure
In certain circumstances under the California “Shine the Light” law, residents of California have the right to opt out of the sharing of certain categories of Personal Data (as defined in the Shine the Light statute) with third parties for their direct marketing purposes. kumu does not share your Personal Data to third parties for the purpose of direct marketing.
Do Not Track
Some browsers have a “do not track” feature that lets you tell websites that you do not want to have your online activities tracked.  At this time, our websites do not respond to browsers’ do not track signals.
Contact information
For questions about our U.S. state data privacy practices, including about how to exercise your data access rights under California law, please contact us at
dpo@kumu.ph
